## Helper Functions

### Extract Values

```{python}
def extract_values(df, purpose, period, pattern, include_veh_categories=True):
    """
    Extract values from dataframe for given purpose/period matching a pattern.

    Parameters:
    -----------
    df : DataFrame
        DataFrame with MultiIndex columns (purpose, period)
    purpose : str
        Purpose to filter (e.g., 'HBW', 'HBO')
    period : str
        Period to filter (e.g., 'PK', 'OK', 'Daily')
    pattern : str
        Pattern to match in index (e.g., 'motor', 'bike', 'transit')
    include_veh_categories : bool
        If True, include all vehicle categories. If False, only include '_all' and strip suffix.

    Returns:
    --------
    dict : {variable_name: value}
    """
    results = {}

    # Check if column exists
    if (purpose, period) not in df.columns:
        return results

    # Filter rows matching pattern
    mask = df.index.str.contains(pattern)

    for idx in df[mask].index:
        value = df.loc[idx, (purpose, period)]

        if include_veh_categories:
            # Include all vehicle categories as-is
            results[idx] = value
        else:
            # Only include '_all' suffix and strip it
            if idx.endswith('_all'):
                # Remove '_all' suffix
                var_name = idx.rsplit('_', 1)[0]
                results[var_name] = value

    return results
```

### Export Function

```{python}
def export_calib_file(purpose, period, export_mode="needed", remove_all_suffix=False):
    """
    Export calibration target file for a given purpose and period.

    Parameters:
    -----------
    purpose : str
        Trip purpose (HBW, HBO, NHB, HBC, HBSch)
    period : str
        Time period (PK, OK, Daily)
    export_mode : str
        Export mode: "all", "comment", "needed"
    remove_all_suffix : bool
        Remove _all suffix when no vehicle disaggregation exists in entire file
    """

    # Determine file period (Daily becomes 'pk' for HBC/HBSch)
    file_period = 'pk' if period == 'Daily' else period.lower()

    # Determine display period for header
    display_period = file_period.capitalize()

    filename = f"calib_target_{purpose.lower()}_{file_period}.txt"
    filepath = os.path.join(output_dir, filename)

    print(f"\nCreating {filename}... (Mode: {export_mode})")

    # Get pattern configuration for this purpose/period
    patterns = variable_veh_patterns.get(purpose, {}).get(period, {})

    # Check if entire file has only 'all' suffix (for suffix removal)
    file_has_only_all = all(
        'all' in patterns.get(var, ['all']) and len(patterns.get(var, ['all'])) == 1
        for var in patterns.keys()
    )
    apply_suffix_removal = remove_all_suffix and file_has_only_all

    # Helper function to get variable name based on settings
    def get_var_name(base_name, veh_cat):
        var_name = f"{base_name}_{veh_cat}"
        if apply_suffix_removal and veh_cat == 'all':
            var_name = base_name
        return var_name

    # Helper function to determine if a variable should be included/commented
    def should_include(var_family, veh_cat):
        """
        Returns tuple: (include, comment)
        - include: whether to write the line
        - comment: whether to prefix with ';'
        """
        # Mode 1: Export everything, no comments
        if export_mode == "all":
            # Exclude 3veh in mode 1 would be incorrect based on user request
            # User said keep 3veh for mode 1
            return (True, False)

        # Get pattern for this variable family
        pattern = patterns.get(var_family, ['all'])

        # For modes 2 and 3, exclude 3veh (it's the base category)
        if veh_cat == '3veh':
            if export_mode == "needed":
                return (False, False)  # Don't include at all
            elif export_mode == "comment":
                return (True, True)  # Include but comment out

        # Mode 2: Export all, comment unused
        if export_mode == "comment":
            if veh_cat in pattern:
                return (True, False)  # Include, no comment
            else:
                return (True, True)   # Include, but commented

        # Mode 3: Only needed
        if export_mode == "needed":
            if veh_cat in pattern:
                return (True, False)  # Include
            else:
                return (False, False) # Don't include

        return (False, False)

    # Helper function to extract and format values
    def extract_and_write(f, df, var_pattern, var_families, section_comment, sub_comment=None):
        """
        Extract values and write to file with proper formatting

        Parameters:
        -----------
        f : file handle
        df : DataFrame with values
        var_pattern : str - pattern to match in index
        var_families : list - list of variable family names (e.g., ['bike', 'walk'])
        section_comment : str - main section comment
        sub_comment : str - optional sub-section comment
        """
        f.write(f"{section_comment}\t\t\n")
        if sub_comment:
            f.write(f"  {sub_comment}\t\t\n")

        has_output = False

        for var_family in var_families:
            # Try all vehicle categories
            for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
                include, comment = should_include(var_family, veh_cat)

                if not include:
                    continue

                # Construct the full variable name in the dataframe
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_{var_family}_{veh_cat}"

                # Check if variable exists in dataframe
                if df_var_name not in df.index:
                    continue

                # Check if column exists
                if (purpose, period) not in df.columns:
                    continue

                value = df.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]

                # Get output variable name (with potential suffix removal)
                output_var_name = get_var_name(f"calib_share_{var_family}", veh_cat)

                # Write the line
                comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")
                has_output = True

        if has_output:
            f.write("\t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

    with open(filepath, 'w') as f:
        # Write header
        f.write(f";Calibration target values - {purpose} {display_period}\t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # Write disclaimer - only for all and comment modes
        if export_mode in ["all", "comment"]:
            f.write(f";Note: Not all of the variables listed below are used directly in the Mode Choice model. Some are included solely for verification and cross-checking purposes.\t\t\n")
            f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 1: Motorized vs Non-motorized (within total trips)
        # =====================================================================
        extract_and_write(
            f, df_alltrips_cat, 'nonmotor_',
            ['nonmotor'],
            ";relative within total trips",
            ";nonmotorized shares "
        )

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 2: Walk vs Bike (within nonmotorized)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within nonmotorized\t\t\n")

        # Walk shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('walk', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_walk_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_nonmotorized_cat.index and (purpose, period) in df_nonmotorized_cat.columns:
                    value = df_nonmotorized_cat.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_walk", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;walk shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # Bike shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('bike', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_bike_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_nonmotorized_cat.index and (purpose, period) in df_nonmotorized_cat.columns:
                    value = df_nonmotorized_cat.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_bike", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;bike shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")

        f.write("\t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 3: Drive Alone vs Shared Ride (within auto)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within auto\t\t\n")

        # Alone shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('alone', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_alone_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_auto_riders.index and (purpose, period) in df_auto_riders.columns:
                    value = df_auto_riders.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_alone", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;drive alone shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # Shared shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('shared', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_shared_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_auto_riders.index and (purpose, period) in df_auto_riders.columns:
                    value = df_auto_riders.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_shared", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;shared ride shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")

        f.write("\t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 4: SR2 vs SR3 (within shared ride)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within shared ride\t\t\n")

        # SR2 shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('sr2', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_sr2_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_shared_by_person.index and (purpose, period) in df_shared_by_person.columns:
                    value = df_shared_by_person.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_sr2", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;sr2 shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # SR3 shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('sr3', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_sr3_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_shared_by_person.index and (purpose, period) in df_shared_by_person.columns:
                    value = df_shared_by_person.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_sr3", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;sr3 shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")

        f.write("\t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 5: Auto vs Transit (within motorized)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within motorized\t\t\n")

        # Auto shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('auto', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_auto_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_motorized_cat.index and (purpose, period) in df_motorized_cat.columns:
                    value = df_motorized_cat.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_auto", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;auto shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # Transit shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('transit', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_transit_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_motorized_cat.index and (purpose, period) in df_motorized_cat.columns:
                    value = df_motorized_cat.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_transit", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;transit shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")
                    if not comment:
                        f.write(" \t\t\n")

        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 6: Transit by Service Type (within transit)
        # Now includes expanded CRT subclasses (CRT00, CRT01, etc.)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within transit\t\t\n")

        # Service types including expanded CRT
        service_types = ['COR', 'BRT', 'LRT', 'EXP'] + [f'CRT{i:02d}' for i in range(9)]

        for service in service_types:
            for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
                include, comment = should_include(service, veh_cat)
                if include:
                    df_var_name = f"calib_share_{service.lower()}_{veh_cat}"
                    # Check with uppercase service name as well
                    if df_var_name not in df_transit_by_service.index:
                        df_var_name = f"calib_share_{service}_{veh_cat}"

                    if df_var_name in df_transit_by_service.index and (purpose, period) in df_transit_by_service.columns:
                        value = df_transit_by_service.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                        output_var_name = get_var_name(f"calib_share_{service}", veh_cat)
                        comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                        f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")

        f.write("  \t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 7: Walk vs Drive Access (within transit)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within transit\t\t\n")

        # Walk access shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('walkacc', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_walkacc_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_transit_by_access.index and (purpose, period) in df_transit_by_access.columns:
                    value = df_transit_by_access.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_walkacc", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;walk-to-transit shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # Drive access shares
        for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
            include, comment = should_include('driveacc', veh_cat)
            if include:
                df_var_name = f"calib_share_driveacc_{veh_cat}"
                if df_var_name in df_transit_by_access.index and (purpose, period) in df_transit_by_access.columns:
                    value = df_transit_by_access.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                    output_var_name = get_var_name("calib_share_driveacc", veh_cat)
                    comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                    if not comment:
                        f.write("  ;drive-to-transit shares \t\t\n")
                    f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")

        f.write("\t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 8: Walk-to-Transit by Service (within walkacc)
        # Now includes expanded CRT subclasses (wCRT00, wCRT01, etc.)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within walkacc\t\t\n")

        # Walk service types including expanded CRT
        walk_services = ['wCOR', 'wBRT', 'wLRT', 'wEXP'] + [f'wCRT{i:02d}' for i in range(9)]

        for service in walk_services:
            for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
                include, comment = should_include(service, veh_cat)
                if include:
                    df_var_name = f"calib_share_{service.lower()}_{veh_cat}"
                    # Check with correct case
                    if df_var_name not in df_walk_to_transit.index:
                        df_var_name = f"calib_share_{service}_{veh_cat}"

                    if df_var_name in df_walk_to_transit.index and (purpose, period) in df_walk_to_transit.columns:
                        value = df_walk_to_transit.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                        output_var_name = get_var_name(f"calib_share_{service}", veh_cat)
                        comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                        f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")

        f.write("\t\t\n")
        f.write("\t\t\n")

        # =====================================================================
        # SECTION 9: Drive-to-Transit by Service (within driveacc)
        # Now includes expanded CRT subclasses (dCRT00, dCRT01, etc.)
        # =====================================================================
        f.write(";relative within driveacc\t\t\n")

        # Drive service types including expanded CRT
        drive_services = ['dCOR', 'dBRT', 'dLRT', 'dEXP'] + [f'dCRT{i:02d}' for i in range(9)]

        for service in drive_services:
            for veh_cat in ['0veh', '1veh', '2veh', '3veh', 'all']:
                include, comment = should_include(service, veh_cat)
                if include:
                    df_var_name = f"calib_share_{service.lower()}_{veh_cat}"
                    # Check with correct case
                    if df_var_name not in df_drive_to_transit.index:
                        df_var_name = f"calib_share_{service}_{veh_cat}"

                    if df_var_name in df_drive_to_transit.index and (purpose, period) in df_drive_to_transit.columns:
                        value = df_drive_to_transit.loc[df_var_name, (purpose, period)]
                        output_var_name = get_var_name(f"calib_share_{service}", veh_cat)
                        comment_prefix = ";" if comment else " "
                        f.write(f"{comment_prefix} {output_var_name:<30}\t=\t{value:.4f}\n")

    print(f"  ✅ Written to {filepath}")
```
